    "question": "In the context of digital design, what is the primary purpose of a finite state machine (FSM)?",
    "options": ["A. To perform arithmetic operations", "B. To manage memory allocation", "C. To control the sequence of operations in a system", "D. To optimize power consumption in digital circuits"],
    "correctIndex": 2,
    "explanation": "A finite state machine (FSM) is used to control the sequence of operations in a digital system. It defines a set of states and transitions between those states based on inputs, which is essential for managing the behavior of digital systems. While FSMs can indirectly contribute to power optimization by enabling efficient control, that is not their primary purpose (option D). FSMs are not typically used for arithmetic operations (option A) or memory management (option B)."
