    "question": "What is the primary role of an arithmetic logic unit (ALU) in a computer's central processing unit (CPU)?",
    "options": ["A. To manage input and output operations", "B. To perform arithmetic and logical operations", "C. To control the flow of instructions in the CPU", "D. To store data and instructions for processing"],
    "correctIndex": 1,
    "explanation": "The arithmetic logic unit (ALU) is responsible for performing arithmetic and logical operations, such as addition, subtraction, AND, OR, etc. It is a fundamental component of the CPU. Managing input/output operations is typically handled by other units (option A). Controlling the flow of instructions is the role of the control unit (option C). Storing data and instructions is the function of memory, not the ALU (option D)."
