    "question": "In digital design, what is the significance of the clock signal in synchronous circuits?",
    "options": ["A. It determines the power consumption of the circuit", "B. It provides a reference for the timing of operations", "C. It directly influences the logical functionality of the circuit", "D. It is used only for debugging purposes in digital systems"],
    "correctIndex": 1,
    "explanation": "The clock signal in synchronous circuits provides a reference for the timing of operations. It ensures that all components of the circuit update their states simultaneously, which helps in avoiding race conditions and ensuring predictable behavior. The clock signal does not directly determine power consumption (option A), although faster clocks can lead to higher power usage. It does not directly influence the logical functionality (option C); that is determined by the combinational logic. Clock signals are essential for operation, not just for debugging (option D)."
  }
